<p>I have a form validation code that detects all DOM elements with the attribute "validate". Which is called pressing the 'submit' button:</p>  <pre><code>$('*[validate]').each(function () {/*validation goes here*/}); </code></pre>  <p>This works perfectly fine.</p>  <p>But also I have two tables, each one has it's own input element with the validate attribute in it and a 'submit' button.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!-- First Table --&gt; &lt;table&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;         &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="text" value="" validate /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;         &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="button" value="Ok" onclick="validate function call here"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt; &lt;table&gt;  &lt;!-- Second Table --&gt; &lt;table&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="text" value="" validate /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="button" value="Ok" onclick="validate function call here"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt; &lt;table&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I validate only the elements that is in the same parent table of the 'submit' button?</p>